# Task router — Update Customer Notes

## When this rule applies

- The user opens or references **`docs/ai/playbooks/update-customer-notes.md`**, or
- The user (or chat) clearly invokes **`Update Customer Notes for [CustomerName]`** (any reasonable casing/spacing for the customer token).

Repo-wide planner/orchestrator behavior stays in **`.cursor/rules/workflow.mdc`** (main Agent). This file only **routes product workflows**; it does **not** redefine subagent delegation or task-plan approval.

## Preferred path: multi-advisor orchestrator

When the user wants the **full Stage 3 pipeline** (sync → structured context → extractor delta → **sequential** domain advisors **SOC → APP → VULN → ASM → AI** → compiled mutations → **human approval** → MCP writes), follow **`.cursor/rules/20-orchestrator.mdc`** end-to-end for **`Update Customer Notes for [CustomerName]`**.

Treat **`[CustomerName]`** as the single customer for the session (**`docs/project_spec.md` §2 Rule 4**). If missing, ask once before deep reads.

## Fallback: monolithic playbook

**`docs/ai/playbooks/update-customer-notes.md`** remains a **supported, documented fallback** (orchestrator vs monolithic checks: **`docs/ai/playbooks/debug-pipeline.md`**). Use it when:

- The user explicitly asks for the **legacy / single-pass** playbook, or
- They need only a subset of steps from that doc without advisor fan-out.

If intent is ambiguous, **prefer** **`20-orchestrator.mdc`** and say so in one line; offer the monolithic playbook as the alternative.

